---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Button from '../../components/Button.astro';
import Card from '../../components/Card.astro';
import Section from '../../components/Section.astro';
import { APP_STORE_URL, isAppStoreUrlKnown, SITE_NAME, getCampaignAppStoreUrl } from '../../lib/site';

const campaignToken = 'seo_en_track_pouch';
const appStoreKnown = isAppStoreUrlKnown(APP_STORE_URL);
const appStoreCtaLabel = appStoreKnown ? 'Download on the App Store' : 'Coming soon on the App Store';
const finalAppStoreUrl = getCampaignAppStoreUrl(campaignToken);
---

<Layout
	title="Track Nicotine Pouches — Simple Pouch Tracker App"
	description="Track your nicotine pouch use with Wean Nicotine. Log ZYN, VELO, On! or any pouch brand in one tap, see weekly trends, and follow a gradual reduction plan."
	canonicalPath="/track-nicotine-pouches/"
	availableLocales={['en']}
>
	<section class="hero">
		<div class="container">
			<h1>Track your nicotine pouch use simply and privately</h1>
			<p class="lede">
				Whether you use ZYN, VELO, On! or another brand, Wean Nicotine helps you track every pouch and see how your use changes over time.
				Log each pouch in one tap and get a clear picture of your daily and weekly patterns.
			</p>
			<div class="cta">
				<Button variant="primary" href={finalAppStoreUrl} disabled={!appStoreKnown} external={true}>
					{appStoreCtaLabel}
				</Button>
				<Button variant="secondary" href="/">Learn more about Wean Nicotine</Button>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<Section id="who" title="Who nicotine pouch tracking is for" lede="If you use nicotine pouches daily and want more awareness or control, tracking is the place to start.">
		<div class="grid-2">
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>You go through cans faster than expected</h3>
				<p>It is easy to lose count. Tracking every pouch helps you see exactly how many you use and where the money goes.</p>
			</Card>
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>You want to cut down from your current level</h3>
				<p>Before you can reduce, you need to know your baseline. Tracking gives you an honest starting point for a <a href="/taper-nicotine/">gradual nicotine taper</a>.</p>
			</Card>
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>You have tried other trackers but they are too generic</h3>
				<p>Wean Nicotine is built specifically for pouch-based nicotine products. No adapting a habit tracker to fit your needs.</p>
			</Card>
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>You value your privacy</h3>
				<p>Wean Nicotine does not require an account, does not sync to the cloud, and does not share your data. Everything stays on your phone.</p>
			</Card>
		</div>
	</Section>

	<Section id="what" title="What Wean Nicotine tracks for you" lede="Focused tracking built for nicotine pouches, not general habits.">
		<div class="grid-3">
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>Pouches per day</h3>
				<p>One tap each time you use a pouch. See your daily total and how many are left in your allowance at any point.</p>
			</Card>
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>Weekly summaries</h3>
				<p>Compare weeks side by side. See total pouches, days within allowance, and overall trend direction.</p>
			</Card>
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>Cost savings</h3>
				<p>Enter your can price and Wean Nicotine shows how much money you save as you reduce. It adds up faster than you think.</p>
			</Card>
		</div>
	</Section>

	<Section id="why" title="Why a dedicated pouch tracker makes a difference" lede="Generic habit trackers were not designed for nicotine reduction.">
		<div class="grid-2">
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>One-tap logging</h3>
				<p>No forms to fill in, no categories to select. Open the app, tap once, done. It takes less than a second.</p>
			</Card>
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>Built-in reduction plan</h3>
				<p>Wean Nicotine does not just count. It gives you a daily allowance that decreases over time, turning tracking into active reduction.</p>
			</Card>
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>Craving support when you need it</h3>
				<p>Reached your daily limit? Wean Nicotine includes <a href="/how-to-handle-nicotine-cravings/">breathing exercises and urge surfing tools</a> to help you get through the moment.</p>
			</Card>
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>Completely offline and private</h3>
				<p>No account, no internet required, no data leaving your device. <a href="/private-quit-nicotine-app/">Your nicotine data stays yours</a>.</p>
			</Card>
		</div>
	</Section>

	<Section id="faq" title="Frequently asked questions about nicotine pouch tracking">
		<div class="grid-2">
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>Does Wean Nicotine work with ZYN, VELO, and other brands?</h3>
				<p>Yes. Wean Nicotine tracks pouches regardless of brand. Whether you use ZYN, VELO, On!, Loop, or snus, the tracking works the same way.</p>
			</Card>
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>Can I track without reducing?</h3>
				<p>Absolutely. You can use Wean Nicotine just to understand your current use. Many people start by tracking for a week before setting a reduction goal.</p>
			</Card>
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>Is there a difference between tracking snus and nicotine pouches?</h3>
				<p>In Wean Nicotine, no. Both are tracked the same way: one tap per pouch. You can also <a href="/track-snus-use/">track snus use</a> with the same app.</p>
			</Card>
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>What does Wean Nicotine cost?</h3>
				<p>Wean Nicotine is a one-time purchase — no subscriptions, no ads, and no data selling. You pay once and get every feature, built by an independent solo developer.</p>
			</Card>
		</div>
	</Section>

	<script type="application/ld+json">
		{
			"@context": "https://schema.org",
			"@type": "BreadcrumbList",
			"itemListElement": [
				{
					"@type": "ListItem",
					"position": 1,
					"name": "Home",
					"item": "https://weannicotine.iamjarl.com"
				},
				{
					"@type": "ListItem",
					"position": 2,
					"name": "Track Nicotine Pouches",
					"item": "https://weannicotine.iamjarl.com/track-nicotine-pouches/"
				}
			]
		}
	</script>

	<section class="bottom-cta">
		<div class="container">
			<h2>Start tracking your nicotine pouch use</h2>
			<p>One tap per pouch. See your patterns, track your progress, and take control.</p>
			<Button variant="primary" href={finalAppStoreUrl} disabled={!appStoreKnown} external={true}>
				{appStoreCtaLabel}
			</Button>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>

<style>
	.hero {
		padding: clamp(54px, 7vw, 96px) 0;
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
	}

	h1 {
		margin: 0 0 var(--space-lg);
		font-size: clamp(36px, 5vw, 48px);
		line-height: 1.1;
		letter-spacing: -0.03em;
	}

	.lede {
		margin: 0 0 var(--space-xl);
		color: var(--text-secondary);
		max-width: 62ch;
		font-size: 18px;
		line-height: 28px;
	}

	.cta {
		display: flex;
		gap: var(--space-md);
		flex-wrap: wrap;
	}

	.grid-2, .grid-3 {
		display: grid;
		gap: var(--space-lg);
	}

	.grid-2 { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr)); }
	.grid-3 { grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr)); }

	h3 {
		margin: 0 0 var(--space-sm);
		font-size: 18px;
		letter-spacing: -0.01em;
	}

	p { margin: 0; color: var(--text-secondary); }

	.bottom-cta {
		padding: clamp(44px, 6vw, 84px) 0;
		text-align: center;
		border-top: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
	}

	.bottom-cta h2 {
		margin: 0 0 var(--space-md);
		font-size: clamp(28px, 3.2vw, 36px);
		letter-spacing: -0.02em;
	}

	.bottom-cta p {
		margin: 0 0 var(--space-xl);
		color: var(--text-secondary);
	}

	@media (max-width: 960px) {
		.grid-3 { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
	}

	@media (max-width: 700px) {
		.grid-2 { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
	}
</style>
